quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  38,1,"Saad* – By oath of the renowned Qur’an, (Alphabet of the Arabic language; Allah and to whomever He reveals, know their precise meanings.)"
  38,2,"In fact, the disbelievers are in false pride and opposition."
  38,3,"Many a generation We did destroy before them – thereupon they cried out whereas it is not the time to escape!"
  38,4,"And they were surprised that a Herald of Warning came to them from among themselves; and the disbelievers said, “He is a magician, a great liar!”"
  38,5,"“Has he made all the Gods into One God? This is really something very strange!”"
  38,6,"And their leaders went about, “Leave him and cling steadfastly to your Gods! Indeed he has a hidden objective in this!”"
  38,7,"“We never heard of this even in Christianity, the latest religion; this is clearly a newly fabricated matter.”"
  38,8,"“Is the Qur’an which is sent to him, among us?” In fact they are in a doubt concerning My Book; in fact, they have not yet tasted My punishment."
  38,9,"Or do they hold the treasures of the mercy of your Lord, the Almighty, the Great Bestower?"
  38,10,"Is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth and all that is between them, for them? So would they not just ascend using ropes?"
  38,11,"This is just one of the disgraced armies, that will be routed there and then."
  38,12,"Before them, the people of Nooh had denied, and the tribe of A’ad, and Firaun who used to crucify."
  38,13,"And the tribe of Thamud, and the people of Lut, and the People of the Woods; these are the groups."
  38,14,"None of them was such that it did not deny the Noble Messengers, therefore My punishment became inevitable."
  38,15,"They await just one Scream, which no one can avert."
  38,16,"And they said, “Our Lord! Give us our share quickly, before the Day of Reckoning.”"
